cbonsai
------------------------------------------
cbonsai is a bonsai tree generator, written in C using ncurses. It
intelligently creates, colors, and positions a bonsai tree, and is entirely
configurable via CLI options-- see usage. There are 2 modes of operation:
static (see finished bonsai tree), and live (see growth step-by-step).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libncursesw10-6.1-1.20190727

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.35.2-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://gitlab.com/jallbrit/cbonsai

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.com/jallbrit/cbonsai/-/archive/v1.0.0/cbonsai-v1.0.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cbonsai-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cbonsai-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cbonsai-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cbonsai-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(cbonsai)
  /usr/bin/cbonsai.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/cbonsai.README
  /usr/share/doc/cbonsai/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/cbonsai/README.md

